MESSAGE assistant FCFS (First-Come-First-Served) is a non-preemptive scheduling algorithm where processes execute in arrival order. First process gets CPU first. Convoy effect happens when a long process blocks shorter ones behind it.

MESSAGE user What is priority inversion?
MESSAGE assistant Priority inversion is when a high-priority process waits for a low-priority process holding a shared lock. The Mars Pathfinder mission had this bug. Solution: priority inheritance protocol.

MESSAGE user Explain Round Robin scheduling
MESSAGE assistant Round Robin gives each process a fixed time slice (time quantum). When quantum expires, process goes to back of queue. Fair, no starvation. Time quantum too large = becomes FCFS. Too small = too many context switches.